headline: 3 Reasons to Sell KMB and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: What a brutal six months it’s been for Kimberly-Clark. The stock has dropped 23.2% and now trades at $107.08, rattling many shareholders. This might have investors contemplating their next move.
